SUMMARY:Court Appointed Special Advocates (CASA) Community Awareness Breakfast
DESCRIPTION:Event Details\n\nJoin Court Appointed Special Advocates (CASA) for breakfast to learn how to participate in the critical advocacy work CASA provides for children who have experienced abuse and neglect and are placed in the foster care system.  \n\nHear from CASA staff and supporters about the crucial and life-changing impact CASA volunteers have on the lives of our community’s most vulnerable children.  \n\nThe Community Awareness Breakfast is open to anyone who wants to learn more about becoming a CASA volunteer\, donor\, or friend. Guests will be given the opportunity to make a contribution. \n\nThis event is free and open to the public\, but registration is required. Please feel free to bring a friend! Please register by March 30\, 2026.\n\nQuestions? Please contact raquel@casalancleb.org \n\n\nWho We Are \n\nCASA of Lancaster and Lebanon Counties recruits and trains citizen volunteers to advocate for the best interests of youth who have suffered abuse and neglect and are in the foster care system. \n\nWe have served over 1\,100 of Lancaster and Lebanon County’s most vulnerable children since our program began in 2009. \n\nOur mission is to provide a qualified and compassionate court-appointed volunteer advocate to every child who is abused and neglected\, to ensure the fundamental human right of having a safe\, nurturing\, and permanent home is met. \n\nTo learn more\, please visit www.casalancleb.org \n            \n        \n                \n                \n    Register Now
URL:https://figlancaster.com/event/court-appointed-special-advocates-casa-community-awareness-breakfast/
LOCATION:DoubleTree Resort\, 2400 Willow Street Pike\, Lancaster\, 17602
CATEGORIES:Community
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://fig.guide/content/uploads/sites/3/2026/03/Lancaster-breakfast-email.avif
ORGANIZER;CN="CASA of Lancaster and Lebanon Counties":MAILTO:margie@casalancleb.org
END:VEVENT
